()Jab bhi koi employee company chhodta hai (Off-board/Leaver) ya delete hota hai, 
toh SailPoint ka standard engine automatic uske owned objects (jaise Application, Role, ya Workgroup)
ka owner hatata nahi hai. Agar hum sahi waqt par unhe re-assign na karein, toh woh saare objects "Orphan" (bina owner ke) ho 
jaate hain, jo ki ek bada security audit issue hai.

Isliye BeanShell script ka use karke hum database se un saare objects ko khinchte hain, 
ek mast HTML table banate hain, aur direct email ke zariye notification bhej dete hain.

Aaiye iska ekdam complete live-project jaisa code aur workflow structure samajhte hain, 
jisme aapke bataye saare objects (Application, Bundle/Role, Workgroup, aur Rule) cover ho jayein:-

Object 1: Email Template XML (OwnedObjectsEmailTemplate.xml):-
Yeh aapka custom email template hai jo automatic HTML format mein bani-banayi table ko render karega.
XML
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE EmailTemplate PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<EmailTemplate name="Identity Offboarding Owner Alert" subject="URGENT: Re-assignment Required for Objects Owned by $identityName">
  <Body>
    <![CDATA[
    <html>
    <body style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #333333;">
      <h2 style="color: #d9534f;">URGENT: Re-assignment Required</h2>
      <p>Dear IAM Governance Team,</p>
      <p>An off-boarding or status change has been detected for user: <strong>$identityName</strong>.</p>
      <p>This user is currently configured as the <strong>OWNER</strong> for critical infrastructure objects in IdentityIQ. To prevent orphan components, please re-assign these items immediately.</p>
      <br/>
      
      <!-- Yahan workflow se direct HTML Table aakar chipak jayegi -->
      $ownedObjectsTable
      
      <br/>
      <p>Regards,<br/>IdentityIQ Governance Automation Team</p>
    </body>
    </html>
    ]]>
  </Body>
</EmailTemplate>

