()"Kya sach mein variables ko if-conditions ke andar hi daalna chahiye, aur isse memory management par kya asar padta hai?"
1. Jab Variables bahar hote hain (Aapka purana tareeka):-
Agar aap code ke shuru mein hi bina check kiye ye lines likh dete hain:-
Java
ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();
Provisioner provisioner = new Provisioner(context);
Toh jaise hi rule run hoga, SailPoint memory (JVM Heap) mein ye dono bade objects turant ban jayenge.
Maan lijiye, iske agla hi step if(identityName == null) par fail ho jata hai aur code wahin se return null; ho jata hai, 
toh kya hua?
Aapka code toh 1 hi millisecond mein band ho gaya...
Lekin memory mein ProvisioningPlan aur Provisioner ke objects faltu mein ban kar baith gaye.
Ab jab tak Java ka Garbage Collector (GC) aakar unhe saaf nahi karega, wo memory block blocked rahegi.

sirf Provisioner ke constructor mein context dena padta hai.jaise=Provisioner project=new Provisioner(context);
