()2. linkks List Initialized Nahi Hai (NullPointerException)
Aapne likha List linkks=null; aur loop ke andar direct linkks.add(linkk); kar diya.
Agar koi List null hai, toh usme data add nahi ho sakta, Beanshell wahi crash ho jayega. 
Isey initialize karna padega: List linkks = new ArrayList();
 
()lin=(Link)linkks;
linkks ek poori List hai, aap poori list ko ek single Link mein cast nahi kar sakte. 
List se ek-ek karke item nikalne ke liye linkks.get(i) karna padega.

note:kyu nahi likhe generic List<Object>,List<Map<"String","Object">>:-
Wajah B: Beanshell Engine Ka Confusion (Strict Typing Bug)
Beanshell ek loosely-typed scripting language hai. Kabhi-kabhi jab aap complex rules mein complex generic types (jaise List<Map<String, Object>>) likhte ho, toh Beanshell ka compiler confuse ho jata hai aur Parse Error ya Signature Not Found Error de deta hai.

💡 SailPoint Mein Best Practice Kya Hai?

🚫 Yeh Chalega (Par mat likho):-
Java
List<Object> linkks = new ArrayList<Object>();

🚫 Agar strict type likhna hi hai (Toh sahi class likho):
Agar aapko batana hi hai ki list mein kya jayega, toh Object ke bajay actual class (Link) likho:
Java
List<Link> linkks = new ArrayList<Link>();
