}

Maan lo user ke paas Active Directory (AD) mein 3 Groups hain: VPN, Email, aur SAP_Access.
Chakkar 1 (Group 1 - VPN): Code ne aqqq request mein VPN group remove karne ka command daala. Aur turant plan.add(aqqq) chal gaya. Master plan ke andar AD ki Pehli Request chali gayi (Isme VPN hai).
Chakkar 2 (Group 2 - Email): Usi aqqq request mein niche Email group remove karne ka command juda. Aur phir se plan.add(aqqq) chal gaya! Ab master plan ke andar AD ki Doosri Request chali gayi (Isme VPN aur Email dono hain).
Chakkar 3 (Group 3 - SAP_Access): Usi request mein SAP_Access juda. Aur phir se plan.add(aqqq) chal gaya! Master plan ke andar AD ki Teesri Request chali gayi (Isme VPN, Email, aur SAP_Access teeno hain).

Sahi Approach Kya Hai? (The Single Entry Rule)
SailPoint ka rule ekdum simple hai: Har application ke liye sirf ek AccountRequest dabba banna chahiye, 
usme chupchaap saare groups bharne chahiye, aur jab saare groups bhar jayein (loop khatam ho jaye), 
tab use poore package ko ek hi baar plan.add(aqqq) karna chahiye.

